    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="choosing-the-wrong-niche"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A niche that is too broad means you compete with established sites with 10,000+ backlinks. A niche that is too narrow means you run out of topics in 3 months.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="neglecting-email-from-the-start">
      <span class="faq-q-text">Neglecting Email from the Start</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="neglecting-email-from-the-start"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Social followers are rented. Email subscribers are owned. Start building your email list on day one. Even 50 subscribers who open your emails are more valuable than 5,000 Twitter followers who never click.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="inconsistent-publishing">
      <span class="faq-q-text">Inconsistent Publishing</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="inconsistent-publishing"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>One post this week, zero next week, three the week after. This pattern confuses readers and search engines. Google rewards consistency. Readers reward consistency.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="how-many-posts-should-i-have-before-launching-my-b">
      <span class="faq-q-text">How many posts should I have before launching my blog?</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="how-many-posts-should-i-have-before-launching-my-b"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Aim for 5–10 posts. Five is the minimum to look like an active blog. Ten gives readers enough content to explore. Quality matters more than quantity. Five excellent posts beat 20 mediocre ones.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="how-long-does-it-take-to-launch-a-blog">
